    <!-- ABOUT -->
    <section id="about">
      <h2>About Angel’s Garden Foundation</h2>
      <p>
        Angel’s Garden Foundation, Inc. is rooted in Christian values of compassion, service, and stewardship.
        We exist to uplift underserved youth by providing the financial, emotional, and spiritual support they
        need to succeed academically and personally.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also extend our mission to the broader community by offering emergency assistance to families
        experiencing hardship. Whether through financial aid, essential resources, or crisis support, we strive
        to be a source of hope and stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Mission</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Strengthen underserved students through scholarships, mentoring, and leadership development.</li>
        <li>Provide Christ‑centered guidance that nurtures character, purpose, and responsibility.</li>
        <li>Support families in crisis with emergency assistance and community care.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Vision</h3>
      <p>
        A future where every young person is equipped, supported, and inspired to become a responsible,
        thriving member of society.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Core Beliefs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Every child deserves access to education and opportunity.</li>
        <li>Mentorship and leadership training transform futures.</li>
        <li>Faith‑based guidance strengthens character and purpose.</li>
        <li>Communities flourish when families in crisis receive support.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- PROGRAMS -->
    <section id="programs">
      <h2>Programs for Youth and Families</h2>
      <p>
        Our programs are designed to empower underserved students, nurture Christ‑centered leadership, and
        provide practical support to families in crisis.
      </p>

      <h3>Student Scholarship Program</h3>
      <p>
        The Student Scholarship Program provides financial support for underserved students pursuing academic
        excellence. Scholarships help cover tuition, books, supplies, and other educational needs so that
        students can focus on learning and growth.
      </p>

      <h3>Christian Mentorship &amp; Leadership Development</h3>
      <p>
        Through one‑on‑one and group mentoring rooted in Christian values, students receive guidance in:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Personal growth and self‑development</li>
        <li>Leadership skills and responsibility</li>
        <li>Academic planning and goal setting</li>
        <li>Character development and integrity</li>
        <li>Faith‑based encouragement and spiritual support</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Youth Empowerment Workshops</h3>
      <p>
        Our workshops equip youth with practical tools for life and leadership, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Life skills and decision‑making</li>
        <li>Career readiness and vocational exploration</li>
        <li>Leadership training and teamwork</li>
        <li>Goal setting and time management</li>
        <li>Community responsibility and service</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Emergency Assistance for Families</h3>
      <p>
        Angel’s Garden Foundation also serves the near community by supporting families in crisis. We respond
        with compassion, resources, and practical help in situations such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sudden financial hardship or loss of income</li>
        <li>Medical emergencies and unexpected expenses</li>
        <li>Temporary housing or essential living needs</li>
        <li>Food, supplies, and basic necessities</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Our goal is to stand alongside families during difficult seasons and help them regain stability and hope.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- GET INVOLVED -->
    <section id="get-involved">
      <h2>Get Involved</h2>
      <p>
        Your involvement helps transform lives. Whether you volunteer, partner, or give, you are planting seeds
        of hope, education, and leadership in the next generation.
      </p>

      <h3>Volunteer</h3>
      <p>
        Serve as a mentor, workshop leader, event helper, or community support volunteer. Your time and presence
        can make a lasting impact on a young person’s life.
      </p>

      <h3>Partner With Us</h3>
      <p>
        Churches, businesses, and community organizations are invited to collaborate with Angel’s Garden
        Foundation to expand our reach and deepen our impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Sponsor a Student</h3>
      <p>
        Directly support a young person’s education and leadership journey by sponsoring a student scholarship
        or mentoring pathway.
      </p>

      <h3>Support Families in Crisis</h3>
      <p>
        Help provide emergency aid to families experiencing hardship. Your generosity can bring relief, dignity,
        and hope in moments of crisis.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- DONATE -->
